item.content:encoded:
[vc_row row_type="2" blox_height="424" blox_image="5100" page_title="page-title-x" blox_dark="true"][vc_column][distance type="4"][distance type="4"][distance type="3"][vc_column_text]

GIVING

We encourage giving as an act of worship.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][distance type="3"][subtitle type="3" subtitle_content="WHY GIVING?"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][distance type="2"][vc_column_text]
TAKING THE STEP OF FAITH
When you participate in online giving, you decide in advance to faithfully give. God always blesses that kind of faith!  
SIMPLIFYING YOUR LIFE
Online giving is simple, easy, and also reduces post office trips, postage costs and weekly/monthly check-writing chores.  
HELPING THE CHURCH TO SERVE OTHERS
When you participate in online giving, you’re also helping to streamline administrative overhead costs – thus, putting more of your dollars to work in the ministries.[/vc_column_text][distance type="3"][testimonial name="John Smith " img="5053" subtitle="Executive Pastor"]Give in order to be blessed. It is, in our vision, a part of our worship to God. He wants us to understand the blessings that come to those who give with a cheerful heart.[/testimonial][distance type="3"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="5105" img_size="full"][distance][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][distance][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][subtitle type="3" subtitle_content="WAYS TO GIVE"][distance][vc_column_text]
WORSHIP SERVICES
During the weekend services (and mid-week services) we have a time of dedicating our tithes and offerings to God in prayer. This is an opportunity to give to God during the service.  
MAIL
We can also mail our tithes and offerings. Our offering envelopes are available at the Welcome Center in the church foyer. The envelopes are pre-addressed with the churches mailing address. Please take time to pray, then simply place your check within the envelope, add a postage stamp and drop in the mailbox  
GIFTS IN KIND
If you have real property, assets, or something you want to bequeath as a gift, please contact John Doe to discuss ahead of time either by e-mail: Doe@youdomain.com or by phone: 123-456-7890.  
ONLINE
It is now possible and convenient to give online (either one time or automatically) using this website. Once again, consider gathering together as a family to dedicate what you give in prayer, asking God to accomplish spiritual results – especially that many would come to faith in Jesus Christ.[/vc_column_text][button color="gray" size="medium" border="true" btn_content="GIVE ONLINE NOW"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][distance][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="2" blox_padding_top="60px" blox_padding_bottom="60px" blox_bgcolor="#f7f7f7"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]

GREETING MESSAGE
Hello and welcome to our church website, it’s always a real joy for us to meet and have new memebers in our church family. Here you will find useful information about our believe. LEARN MORE ABOUT OUR FAITH COMMUNITY

We are image-bearers: like Father, like daughter, we take Christ in us to our community, revealing His love and grace to a broken world. We hope you’ll join us as we grow in our relationship with Jesus together. If you have questions, please feel free to contact me at any time. Let us think of ways to motivate one another to acts of love and good works. And let us not neglect our meeting together, as some people do, but encourage one another, especially now that the day of His return is drawing near.” - Hebrews 10:24-25 (New Living Translation)[/vc_column_text][distance type="1"][vc_single_image image="5237" border_color="grey" img_link_large="" img_link_target="_self" img_size="full"][distance type="1"][vc_column_text]Experience heartfelt worship, good friends and a refreshing look into God’s Word in a comfortable, casual setting. Spring, Summer, and Fall semesters offered. Church is committed to coming alongside families in a way that helps strengthen and grow them. We know that well-refreshed moms make well-refreshed families, and that is what Moments is all about. We look forward to connecting with you and growing with you as we experience God’s love together through moments. Spring and Fall semesters offered.[/vc_column_text][button url="#" target="_self" color="gray" size="medium" border="true"]CLICK HERE TO JOIN WOMEN MINISTRY[/button][distance type="4"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][subtitle type="3"]MINISTRY LEADER[/subtitle][distance type="1"][ourteam type="1" img="5531" name="Victoria Shafer" title="Women's Ministry Director" text="nteger ac commodo ipsum, sed suscipit massa. [/vc_column_text][distance][vc_column_text]A place where a person with no church background can come and feel comfortable and enjoy the service because the atmosphere will be friendly.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
What is

OUR MISSION

[/vc_column_text][distance][vc_column_text]Our mission statement can be summed up in one word: reach. We reach up through worship, serve God by serving each other to bless.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]

OUR VALUES

[/vc_column_text][distance][vc_column_text]We aim to take a different approach in reaching out and helping people along the journey. We stress cultural relevancy and utilize all medias.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="2" blox_height="387" blox_image="7550" blox_dark="true" row_color="rgba(63,63,63,0.95)"][vc_column][distance type="4"][vc_column_text]

Sometimes the smallest step in the rightdirection, ends up being the biggest step of your life.

  We’d love to meet you! Stop by GUEST CENTRAL in the lobby to grab a cup of coffee, meet someone new, ask a question or get connected at The Father’s House. How is our church different than other churches?

One of distinct thing about our church is what we’re an all- generations community. there’s a place for you here. Click Here to learn more about us (Mission, Vision and core Values)[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/12"][/vc_column][vc_column width="5/12"][vc_column_text]

Who is the Lead Pastor?

Dr. John Doe has been the Lead Pastor here since 2009. Click Here to get to know a bit about him! He is looking for ways to build bridges to a cynical and jaded society.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/1"][distance type="4"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" video_fullscreen="true" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_dark="false" parallax_speed="6" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="7/12"][vc_gmaps link="#E-8_" size="600"][/vc_column][vc_column width="5/12"][big_title type="1" heading="2" aligncenter="" bigtitle_content="First Visit Plan"][vc_column_text]We’re so glad you’ve decided to visit us! You’ll find a list of commonly questions. Please don’t hesitate to send us a message or give us a call at (001) 123-4456

How do I get there?

You can find detailed schedule information and directions below.

What should I wear?

Our church has a “come as you are” atmosphere. You will see some dressed up; some dressed casual. We have no expectations for attire.[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner el_class="" width="1/2"][vc_column_text]

[icon name="fa-clock-o" size="18px" color="#81d742" link=""]  Service Time

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
Modern Services
Saturdays 5:30 p.m. Sundays 11:11 a.m.
Classic Services
Sundays 8:00 and 9:30 a.m.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class="" width="1/2"][vc_column_text]

[icon name="li_location" size="18px" color="#81d742" link=""] Where We Meet

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
Solace Church
12345 North Central Expy New York, NY 54321 Get Directions[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/1"][distance type="4"][big_title type="1" heading="3" aligncenter="" bigtitle_content="Starting Point"][distance type="1"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner el_class="" width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
If you’re interested in getting connected at our church or involved in the life of the church, Starting Point is your first step.
  During our time together, you'll meet our staff, learn how to get involved and understand key truths of the Christian faith. This class is designed to be a conversational environment where you discover more about our church and our mission as a church. Starting Point is held Sundays at 9:00 am in the Café and includes a free breakfast.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class="" width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
How do I get involved?
  There are many ways to get involved. Here are four of them: 1) Come to a worship service on the weekend. 2) Look into joining a Small Group, and get to know some great people. 3) Come to Wednesday Night Together, and enjoy a meal with the church family. 4) Find a Serve opportunity, Here, Near or Far.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/1"][distance type="4"][/vc_column][/vc_row]

What we believe about giving is: We encourage giving as an act of worship
  It focuses our hearts on our true treasure which is Christ (Matthew 6:21) It is an acknowledgement that God is the owner of everything. It turns our focus from the idolatry of money to serving God (Luke 16:11-13) It is an expression of our love for God and our devotion to Him. It is born out of our free response to all He has done for us, not out of guilt or duty.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="5373" img_size="full"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_separator border_width="5"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][distance type="2"][vc_column_text]

SMALL GROUP

LEARN MORE ABOUT OUR FAITH COMMUNITY

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/1"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/1"][distance type="4"][subtitle type="3"]ABOUT SMALL GROUPS[/subtitle][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="5658" border_color="grey" img_link_large="" img_link_target="_self" img_size="full"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][distance type="1"][vc_column_text]

A Quick Review

People grow best when they are connected in healthy small groups. We were never intended to live life alone,but we were created for relationships. accumsan ipsum et nibh rhoncus, eget tempus sapien ultricies. Donec mollis nimb Cras luctus interdum sodales. Quisque quis odio. Sedes sit amet neque malesuada, lobortis commodo magna ntesque pharetra metus vivera sagittis Nullam placerat. We are a community who want to follow Jesus. We would love you to come and be amongst us. We are a community who want to follow Jesus. We would love you to come and be amongst us.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/1"][distance type="1"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="2/3"][distance type="1"][subtitle type="3"]WHAT ARE SMALL GROUPS[/subtitle][distance type="1"][vc_column_text]Small Groups are made of 5-6 couples or eight to twelve individuals who gather to study God’s Word and discuss the issues and challenges of life that we all face. It is also where we pray and care for one another and where you are missed when you are not there. Small Groups come in all shapes and sizes – married couples, singles, men’s, women’s, children, no children, workplace, young adult or empty nesters.[/vc_column_text][distance type="4"][subtitle type="3"]PURPOSE OF SMALL GROUPS[/subtitle][distance type="1"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner el_class="" width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="5552" border_color="grey" img_link_large="" img_link_target="_self" img_size="full"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class="" width="1/2"][vc_column_text]

Life change can

happen here

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]There are five essentials components you will see in our small groups:[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
  • Life Chang
  • Cultivate Relationships
  • Promote Participation
  • Provide Care
  • Identify Future Leaders
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][distance type="4"][subtitle type="3"]HOW TO JOIN A SMALL GROUP[/subtitle][vc_column_text]We know it can be difficult to take the next step from a large group environment like our weekend worship experience to a smaller setting. That’s why we would like to offer a few suggestions to help.   1) Register for our Men’s or Women’s ministry. Click ether of these links to begin the process. Women’s Ministry and Men’s Ministry 2) Volunteering is a great way to meet people who are already plugged into a small group. View Volunteer Opportunities[/vc_column_text][distance type="4"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3" css=".vc_custom_1434371163129{background-color: #f8f8f8 !important;background-position: 0 0 !important;background-repeat: repeat !important;}"][distance type="1"][subtitle type="3"]QUICK FIND[/subtitle][distance type="1"][iconbox type="1" icon_title="BECOME A MEMBER" icon_link_text="READ MORE" icon_link_url="#" icon_name="none"]Le terme adwords désigne l’offre publicitaire de Google, qui consiste en I’ achat de mots-clés pour diffuser une publicité de manière…[/iconbox][distance type="3"][iconbox type="1" icon_title="GET BAPTIZED" icon_link_text="READ MORE" icon_link_url="#" icon_name="none"]Le terme adwords désigne l’offre publicitaire de Google, qui consiste en I’ achat de mots-clés pour diffuser une publicité de manière…[/iconbox][distance type="3"][iconbox type="1" icon_title="ESSENTIAL CLASSES" icon_link_text="READ MORE" icon_link_url="#" icon_name="none"]Le terme adwords désigne l’offre publicitaire de Google, qui consiste en I’ achat de mots-clés pour diffuser une publicité de manière…[/iconbox][distance type="3"][iconbox type="1" icon_title="VOLENTEER" icon_link_text="READ MORE" icon_link_url="#" icon_name="none"]Le terme adwords désigne l’offre publicitaire de Google, qui consiste en I’ achat de mots-clés pour diffuser une publicité de manière…[/iconbox][distance type="3"][iconbox type="1" icon_title="NEED PRAYER" icon_link_text="READ MORE" icon_link_url="#" icon_name="none"]Le terme adwords désigne l’offre publicitaire de Google, qui consiste en I’ achat de mots-clés pour diffuser une publicité de manière…[/iconbox][distance type="3"][/vc_column][/vc_row]

WHO WE ARE

ABOUT OUR CHURCH

BRIEF FROM HISTORY

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]With a passion and zeal for the lost and hurting world, our church is looking for ways to build bridges to a cynical and jaded society. We aim to take a different approach in reaching out and helping people along the journey. We stress cultural relevancy and utilize all medias and means to communicate the the church message. It’s very important to believe that you’re the one. [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/2"][distance type="3"][subtitle type="3" subtitle_content="OUR VISION"][distance type="1"][vc_column_text]A place where a person with no church background can come and feel comfortable and enjoy the service because the atmosphere will be friendly. The sermons are always practical, biblical and relevant. The music is contemporary and upbeat with a praise team and full band.
These dreams are being fulfilled because they are inspired by God!
A church that is fun for the entire family, a church where kids want to go because they have a great time experiencing God’s love. A church that builds families.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][distance type="3"][subtitle type="3" subtitle_content="OUR MISSION"][distance type="1"][vc_column_text]Our mission statement can be summed up in one word: REACH. Reaching Up | Loving God: Vertical reach to touch God. We reach up through worship. Reach In | Serving Each Other: Horizontal reach to bless others.We serve God by serving each other. item.title: Giving - Pax
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row row_type="2" blox_height="424" blox_image="6887" page_title="page-title-x" blox_dark="true"][vc_column][distance type="4"][distance type="4"][distance type="3"][vc_column_text]

GIVING

We encourage giving as an act of worship.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][distance type="4"][vc_column_text]

What we believe about giving

Our mission is leading people in a growing relationship with Jesus Christ. Please join our church repair plan. We appreciate your generosity and your cooperation in supporting our church to spread its community ans service opportunities. [/vc_column_text][distance type="3"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][vc_column_text]

WORSHIP SERVICES
During the weekend services (and mid-week services) we have a time of dedicating our tithes and offerings to God in prayer. This is an opportunity to give to God during the service.  
MAIL
We can also mail our tithes and offerings. Our offering envelopes are available at the Welcome Center in the church foyer. The envelopes are pre-addressed with the churches mailing address. Please take time to pray, then simply place your check within the envelope, add a postage stamp and drop in the mailbox [/vc_column_text][distance][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
GIFTS IN KIND
If you have real property, assets, or something you want to bequeath as a gift, please contact John Doe to discuss ahead of time either by e-mail: Doe@youdomain.com or by phone: 123-456-7890.  
ONLINE
It is now possible and convenient to give online (either one time or automatically) using this website. Once again, consider gathering together as a family to dedicate what you give in prayer, asking God to accomplish spiritual results – especially that many would come to faith in Jesus Christ.[/vc_column_text][distance][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][distance type="3"][subtitle type="3" subtitle_content="WHY GIVING?"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][distance type="2"][vc_column_text]
TAKING THE STEP OF FAITH
When you participate in online giving, you decide in advance to faithfully give. God always blesses that kind of faith!  
SIMPLIFYING YOUR LIFE
Online giving is simple, easy, and also reduces post office trips, postage costs and weekly/monthly check-writing chores.  
HELPING THE CHURCH TO SERVE OTHERS
When you participate in online giving, you’re also helping to streamline administrative overhead costs – thus, putting more of your dollars to work in the ministries.[/vc_column_text][distance type="3"][testimonial name="John Smith " img="5053" subtitle="Executive Pastor"]Give in order to be blessed. It is, in our vision, a part of our worship to God. He wants us to understand the blessings that come to those who give with a cheerful heart.[/testimonial][distance type="3"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="5105" img_size="full"][distance][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][distance][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="2" blox_padding_top="60px" blox_padding_bottom="60px" blox_bgcolor="#f7f7f7"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]

ONE-TIME DONATION

No registration or account needed. Donate with Visa, MasterCard or Discover[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" el_class="alignright"][distance][donate id="5250" size="large" donate_content="DONATE"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][distance][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][distance type="2"][vc_column_text]

DONATE FOR A CAUSE

[vc_row][vc_column][distance type="2"][subtitle type="2" subtitle_content="WHY WE GIVE"][distance][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][distance type="2"][vc_column_text]

OVERVIEW

Give in order to be blessed. It is, in our vision, a part of our worship to God.

God wants us to understand the blessings that come to those who give with a cheerful heart.  

TAKING THE STEP OF FAITH

When you participate in online giving, you decide in advance to faithfully give. God always blesses that kind of faith!

SIMPLIFYING YOUR LIFE

Online giving is simple, easy, and also reduces post office trips, postage costs and weekly/monthly check-writing chores.

HELPING THE CHURCH TO SERVE OTHERS

When you participate in online giving, you’re also helping to streamline administrative overhead costs – thus, putting more of your dollars to work in the ministries![/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="64" img_size="full"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][distance type="2"][vc_separator][distance type="4"][distance type="2"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][acause][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][distance type="4"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][subtitle type="2" subtitle_content="WAYS TO GIVE"][distance][vc_single_image image="72" img_size="full"][distance][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]

You’ll find a list of commonly asked questions. Please don’t hesitate to send us a message or give us a call at (001) 123-4456
How do I get there?
You can find detailed schedule information and directions below.
Where should I park?
If you’re attending the main campus, you can enter onto our “ring road” from New York. From there, our parking team will escort you to the closest available parking spot. We also offer parking trams if you need to park far away, or have a special need.
What should I wear?
Our church has a “come as you are” atmosphere. You will see some dressed up; some dressed casual. We have no expectations for attire.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="5/12"][vc_gmaps link="#E-8_" size="400"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/1"][distance type="2"][distance type="4"][subtitle type="2" subtitle_content="STARTING POINT"][distance type="1"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
If you’re interested in getting connected at our church or involved in the life of the church, Starting Point is your first step.
During our time together, you'll meet our staff, learn how to get involved, and understand key truths of the Christian faith. This class is designed to be a conversational environment where you discover more about our church and our mission as a church. Starting Point is held Sundays at 9:00 am in the Café and includes a free breakfast.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
How do I get involved?
There are many ways to get involved. Here are four of them: 1) Come to a worship service on the weekend. 2) Look into joining a Small Group, and get to know some great people. 3) Come to Wednesday Night Together, and enjoy a meal with the church family. 4) Find a Serve opportunity, Here, Near or Far.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/1"][distance type="2"][/vc_column][/vc_row]

1923

Tracing The Village’s history takes us back to the heart of our mission—to bring glory to God by making disciples through gospel-centered worship, gospel-centered community, gospel-centered service and gospel-centered multiplication.

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]. . .[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]

2015

1845

Tracing The Village’s history takes us back to the heart of our mission—to bring glory to God by making disciples through gospel-centered worship, gospel-centered community, gospel-centered service and gospel-centered multiplication.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]. . .[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]

2015

After much prayer we transitioned the 170 year old church into a new effort called The Church - A gate to God. We now have a missional emphasis using hiking, biking and various outdoors means to reach, teach, and love people with the love of Christ.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/12"][/vc_column][vc_column width="7/12"][vc_single_image border_color="grey" img_link_large="" img_link_target="_self" image="23" img_size="full"][distance type="2"][vc_single_image border_color="grey" img_link_large="" img_link_target="_self" image="22" img_size="full"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/1"][distance type="1"][distance type="4"][subtitle type="2" subtitle_content="CORE VALUES"][distance type="2"][vc_single_image image="25" border_color="grey" img_link_large="" img_link_target="_self" img_size="full"][distance type="2"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]

OUR MISSION

The mission of the church is to glorify God by making disciples through the gospel of Jesus Christ. God’s mission and the mission of His Church are inseparably linked.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]

OUR VISION

There is one God, who exists eternally in a fellowship of three distinct and equal persons: Father, Son, and Holy Spirit who are unchangeable in their holiness, justice, wisdom and love.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/1"][distance][distance type="4"][subtitle type="2" subtitle_content="OUR STAFF"][distance][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="0" row_id="" blox_height="" video_fullscreen="true" blox_image="" blox_bg_attachment="false" blox_cover="true" blox_repeat="no-repeat" align_center="" page_title="" blox_padding_top="" blox_padding_bottom="" blox_dark="false" blox_class="" blox_bgcolor="" parallax_speed="6" video_url="" video_type="video/youtube" video_pattern="true" row_pattern="" row_color="" maxslider_image1="" maxslider_image2="" maxslider_image3="" maxslider_image4="" maxslider_image5="" maxslider_parallax="true" maxslider_pattern="true"][vc_column width="1/4"][ourteam type="1" img="31" name="Nanette Deryer" link="#" title="Associate Pastor" text="Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit.
